      "Metals react with oxygen to form metal oxides (mostly basic).",
      "Non-metals react with oxygen to form non-metal oxides (acidic/neutral).",
      "The Reactivity Series determines if a displacement reaction occurs."
    ],
    "detailedContent": "When elements react, they follow specific patterns. Metals like Magnesium burn brightly in air to form white powders (oxides). Non-metals like Carbon burn to form gases (CO2). The key concept is the 'Reactivity Series': a list of metals ordered by how easily they lose electrons. A metal higher in the series can push out a metal lower in the series from its salt solution. For example, Iron (higher) pushes Copper (lower) out of Copper Sulfate, turning the blue solution green."
